The Argentine Chamber of Phonograms and Videograms Producers (lang-es|Cámara Argentina de Productores de Fonogramas y Videogramas, CAPIF) is an Argentina|Argentine organization member of the IFPI, which represents the music industry in the country. It is a nonprofit organization integrated by multinational and independent record labels.<ref>[http://www.capif.org.ar/Default.asp?CodOp=QSQS&CO=6 "Qué es CAPIF <nowiki>[What is CAPIF]</nowiki>"] webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20111006043246/http://www.capif.org.ar/Default.asp?CodOp=QSQS&CO=6 |date=2011-10-06  (in Spanish). CAPIF. Retrieved May 19, 2010.</ref>

 Sales certification 

CAPIF launched its Gold and Platinum certification program in 1980. Initially, albums required to sell 30,000 units to become Gold and 60,000 units to become Platinum. CAPIF, however, lowered its certification levels in the beginning of 2001 to reflect the declining sales in the recording industry.<ref name="CAPIF certification levels">cite web|url=http://www.capif.org.ar/Default.asp?CodOp=ESOP&CO=5 |title=Discos de Oro y Platino |trans-title=Gold and Platinum discs |work=CAPIF |accessdate=2013-03-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706084412/http://www.capif.org.ar/Default.asp?CodOp=ESOP&CO=5 |archivedate=July 6, 2011 </ref>

